{"questionId":"33284361","questionHtml":"<p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>16</mn><mtext>i</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math> &nbsp; and &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arg </mtext><mfenced><mrow><mn>16</mn><mtext>i</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use De Moivre’s Theorem&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mtext>i</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to find other solutions using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mtext>i</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math> or equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mtext>i</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math> (or any other root)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mtext>i</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math> &nbsp; and &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>13</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mtext>i</mtext><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>13</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award a maximum of <strong><em>(A1)(M1)A1(M1)A1A0</em></strong> for more than four roots or any roots outside the range.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Allow use of r-cis form throughout.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33284361","refere